Title:
Portable Executable (PE) Format Deep Dive (Headers, Sections, Data Directories) + Homemade PE Parser

Type:
Blog Post

Short Summary (4–8 sentences max):
This write-up is a detailed walkthrough of the Windows Portable Executable (PE) format motivated by a failed attempt to run an EXE purely from memory (reflective loading). It explains how a PE is laid out on disk and how key metadata is used by the Windows loader, focusing on DOS/NT/Optional headers, section headers, and core data directories. The author breaks down import resolution (INT/IAT thunks), exports (primarily for DLLs), and base relocations (IMAGE_BASE_RELOCATION blocks and entry types like IMAGE_REL_BASED_DIR64). It also covers RVA-to-file-offset translation using section table metadata (VirtualAddress, VirtualSize, PointerToRawData). The post culminates in building a simple PE parser using winnt.h structures and demonstrates output against a sample EXE, a sample DLL, and ntdll.dll. Useful for red teamers/malware developers implementing loaders/injectors and for reverse engineers needing a practical PE-structure refresher.

Technical Focus:
- PE headers: IMAGE_DOS_HEADER, IMAGE_NT_HEADERS, IMAGE_OPTIONAL_HEADER (PE32+)
- Data directories: Import Table, Export Table, Base Relocation Table, IAT
- Import resolution internals: IMAGE_IMPORT_DESCRIPTOR, IMAGE_THUNK_DATA, INT vs IAT
- Relocations: IMAGE_BASE_RELOCATION blocks, relocation entry parsing, IMAGE_REL_BASED_DIR64
- Sections and memory mapping metadata: IMAGE_SECTION_HEADER, characteristics/protections
- Address translation: RVA/VA/ImageBase concepts and RVA→Raw File Offset conversion

Use Cases:
- Implementing reflective PE loading / custom in-memory loaders
- Writing PE parsing utilities for triage, tooling, or implant staging
- Reverse engineering PE layout issues (entry point, imports, relocations)
- Validating/inspecting imports/exports/relocs for malware analysis
- Debugging process injection approaches that fail due to improper mapping

Keywords:
Portable Executable, PE32+, IMAGE_DOS_HEADER, e_lfanew, IMAGE_NT_HEADERS64, IMAGE_OPTIONAL_HEADER64, ImageBase, AddressOfEntryPoint, RVA, VA, section alignment, file alignment, IMAGE_SECTION_HEADER, data directories, IMAGE_IMPORT_DESCRIPTOR, Import Address Table, IAT, OriginalFirstThunk, FirstThunk, IMAGE_THUNK_DATA64, GetProcAddress, LoadLibraryW, IMAGE_EXPORT_DIRECTORY, IMAGE_BASE_RELOCATION, IMAGE_REL_BASED_DIR64, reflective loading, WriteProcessMemory, CreateRemoteThread, CreateProcess